  "prompt": "Where can I get scholarship for data science in Asia?",
  "response": "Securing a scholarship for data science in Asia can be an excellent way to advance your education without bearing the full financial burden. Here are some options you might consider:\n\n1. **University Scholarships**:\n   - Many universities across Asia offer scholarships for international and domestic students pursuing data science. Look at top institutions known for their data science programs, such as the National University of Singapore (NUS), The University of Tokyo, Tsinghua University, and the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST).\n\n2. **Government Scholarships**:\n   - Some Asian countries have government-sponsored scholarships for international students. Examples include the Chinese Government Scholarship, Japan's MEXT Scholarship, the Korea Global Scholarship Program (GKS), and the Singapore Ministry of Education's Tuition Grant Scheme.\n\n3. **Organization and Foundation Scholarships**:\n   - Certain organizations and foundations provide scholarships targeted at students in specific fields or regions. For instance, the Asian Development Bank\u2013Japan Scholarship Program (ADB-JSP) provides opportunities for postgraduate students.\n\n4. **Online Platforms**:\n   - Websites like Scholarships.com, StudyAbroad.com, and Scholarship-Positions.com often list available scholarships globally, including those aimed at data science students in Asia.\n\n5. **Corporate Scholarships**:\n   - Some technology companies and multinational corporations offer scholarships or financial aid programs for students pursuing studies in data science or related fields. Look for opportunities from companies like Google, Microsoft, and IBM.\n\nWhen applying for scholarships, make sure to check the specific eligibility requirements and deadlines. Also, consider reaching out directly to the university\u2019s financial aid office or the scholarship provider for personalized advice and up-to-date information.",
